#***REMOVED***@jridgewell/sourcemap-codec

Encode/decode***REMOVED***the***REMOVED***`mappings`***REMOVED***property***REMOVED***of***REMOVED***a***REMOVED***[sourcemap](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1U1RGAehQwRypUTovF1KRlpiOFze0b-_2gc6fAH0KY0k/edit).


##***REMOVED***Why?

Sourcemaps***REMOVED***are***REMOVED***difficult***REMOVED***to***REMOVED***generate***REMOVED***and***REMOVED***manipulate,***REMOVED***because***REMOVED***the***REMOVED***`mappings`***REMOVED***property***REMOVED***–***REMOVED***the***REMOVED***part***REMOVED***that***REMOVED***actually***REMOVED***links***REMOVED***the***REMOVED***generated***REMOVED***code***REMOVED***back***REMOVED***to***REMOVED***the***REMOVED***original***REMOVED***source***REMOVED***–***REMOVED***is***REMOVED***encoded***REMOVED***using***REMOVED***an***REMOVED***obscure***REMOVED***method***REMOVED***called***REMOVED***[Variable-length***REMOVED***quantity](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Variable-length_quantity).***REMOVED***On***REMOVED***top***REMOVED***of***REMOVED***that,***REMOVED***each***REMOVED***segment***REMOVED***in***REMOVED***the***REMOVED***mapping***REMOVED***contains***REMOVED***offsets***REMOVED***rather***REMOVED***than***REMOVED***absolute***REMOVED***indices,***REMOVED***which***REMOVED***means***REMOVED***that***REMOVED***you***REMOVED***can't***REMOVED***look***REMOVED***at***REMOVED***a***REMOVED***segment***REMOVED***in***REMOVED***isolation***REMOVED***–***REMOVED***you***REMOVED***have***REMOVED***to***REMOVED***understand***REMOVED***the***REMOVED***whole***REMOVED***sourcemap.

This***REMOVED***package***REMOVED***makes***REMOVED***the***REMOVED***process***REMOVED***slightly***REMOVED***easier.


##***REMOVED***Installation

```bash
npm***REMOVED***install***REMOVED***@jridgewell/sourcemap-codec
```


##***REMOVED***Usage

```js

assert.deepEqual(***REMOVED***decoded,***REMOVED***[
	//***REMOVED***the***REMOVED***first***REMOVED***line***REMOVED***(of***REMOVED***the***REMOVED***generated***REMOVED***code)***REMOVED***has***REMOVED***no***REMOVED***mappings,
	//***REMOVED***as***REMOVED***shown***REMOVED***by***REMOVED***the***REMOVED***starting***REMOVED***semi-colon***REMOVED***(which***REMOVED***separates***REMOVED***lines)
	[],

	//***REMOVED***the***REMOVED***second***REMOVED***line***REMOVED***contains***REMOVED***four***REMOVED***(comma-separated)***REMOVED***segments
	[
		//***REMOVED***segments***REMOVED***are***REMOVED***encoded***REMOVED***as***REMOVED***you'd***REMOVED***expect:
		//***REMOVED***[***REMOVED***generatedCodeColumn,***REMOVED***sourceIndex,***REMOVED***sourceCodeLine,***REMOVED***sourceCodeColumn,***REMOVED***nameIndex***REMOVED***]

		//***REMOVED***i.e.***REMOVED***the***REMOVED***first***REMOVED***segment***REMOVED***begins***REMOVED***at***REMOVED***column***REMOVED***2,***REMOVED***and***REMOVED***maps***REMOVED***back***REMOVED***to***REMOVED***the***REMOVED***second***REMOVED***column
		//***REMOVED***of***REMOVED***the***REMOVED***second***REMOVED***line***REMOVED***(both***REMOVED***zero-based)***REMOVED***of***REMOVED***the***REMOVED***0th***REMOVED***source,***REMOVED***and***REMOVED***uses***REMOVED***the***REMOVED***0th
		//***REMOVED***name***REMOVED***in***REMOVED***the***REMOVED***`map.names`***REMOVED***array
		[***REMOVED***2,***REMOVED***0,***REMOVED***2,***REMOVED***2,***REMOVED***0***REMOVED***],

		//***REMOVED***the***REMOVED***remaining***REMOVED***segments***REMOVED***are***REMOVED***4-length***REMOVED***rather***REMOVED***than***REMOVED***5-length,
		//***REMOVED***because***REMOVED***they***REMOVED***don't***REMOVED***map***REMOVED***a***REMOVED***name
		[***REMOVED***4,***REMOVED***0,***REMOVED***2,***REMOVED***4***REMOVED***],
		[***REMOVED***6,***REMOVED***0,***REMOVED***2,***REMOVED***5***REMOVED***],
		[***REMOVED***7,***REMOVED***0,***REMOVED***2,***REMOVED***7***REMOVED***]
	],

	//***REMOVED***the***REMOVED***final***REMOVED***line***REMOVED***contains***REMOVED***two***REMOVED***segments
	[
		[***REMOVED***2,***REMOVED***1,***REMOVED***10,***REMOVED***19***REMOVED***],
		[***REMOVED***12,***REMOVED***1,***REMOVED***11,***REMOVED***20***REMOVED***]
	]
]);

var***REMOVED***encoded***REMOVED***=***REMOVED***encode(***REMOVED***decoded***REMOVED***);
assert.equal(***REMOVED***encoded,***REMOVED***';EAEEA,EAAE,EAAC,CAAE;ECQY,UACC'***REMOVED***);
```
